{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"title":"Naan Bread","content":["Place flour, yoghurt, milk, oil, sugar, salt and yeast in mixing bowl then mix <b>20 sec\/speed 3<b>. Knead <b>3 min\/<b>. Meanwhile, grease a large bowl with oil. Transfer kneaded dough to prepared bowl. Cover with cling film and leave in a warm place until doubled in size (approx. 1-2 hours). Meanwhile, clean mixing bowl and prepare filling."]},{"title":"Peshwari Naan Filling","content":["Place almonds in mixing bowl and grind <b>15 sec\/speed 10<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add coconut and sultanas then mix <b>10 sec\/\/speed 2<b>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside.","Once dough has doubled in size, preheat grill to 220°C and place a baking tray in bottom of grill to heat.","Divide dough into 8 equal-sized pieces then roll out into circles (Ø 15 cm). Place 1½ Tbsp filling over half the dough. Wet edges with a little milk then fold circles in half and seal. Roll out each to a teardrop shape (approx. 18 cm x 10 cm).","Place naans on preheated baking tray, in batches if necessary, and grill for 2-3 minutes (220°C) until puffed with brown patches. Turn naans over and grill for a further 2 minutes (220°C) until cooked. Transfer to a wire rack then drizzle honey and scatter flaked almonds over hot naans. Serve immediately, while still warm."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Naan Bread","content":["450 g strong white bread flour","200 g plain yoghurt","100 g milk, plus extra for sealing","30 g vegetable oil, plus extra for greasing","1 tsp caster sugar","1 tsp fine sea salt","1 tsp dried instant yeast"]},{"title":"Peshwari Naan Filling","content":["75 g blanched almonds","25 g desiccated coconut","30 g sultanas","2 Tbsp runny honey, for garnish","2 Tbsp flaked almonds, for garnish"]}],"id":"r111571","imageLink":"https:\/\/4.bp.blogspot.com\/-Vy4IHH2EsKY\/XZWYuXlQtSI\/AAAAAAAAeCc\/7ZR9ltCi8jkMFc5lrjb1a6riYz4YjEaQQCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_Iyt-1f1RIXOdhGh7.png","title":"Peshwari Naans","publishedAt":"2017-04-01T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"11.4 g","fat":"13.1 g","uom":"per 1 piece","carbohydrates":"49.6 g","calories":"1511 kJ \/ 361 kcal"},"usefulItems":"cling film, large bowl, baking tray, rolling pin, wire rack, grill","hintsAndTricks":["Ungarnished naans can be reheated on the same day by sprinkling with a few drops of water and placing in a hot oven for 5 minutes.","This sweet variation on the classic flatbread contains an almond, coconut and sultana filling – flavours which provide the perfect balance to spiced dishes. This version has become a firm favourite among our curry houses. Best eaten warm."],"basicInfo":["medium","25m","2h","8 pieces"]}